data.text:
4 years passed. I might be lonely but I'm living, effortlessly. It was midnight, here in Kamaya City, when a dead drunk person came at me and started blabbering.
.
"Isn't it ironic that people are wanting to die so badly, when in reality they just wanted to start living"
.
He left after he said that.

That sentence that made me run outside the bar towards my apartment, sobbing along the way.

I looked inside the mirror. I cut my hair short and I took off my green lenses and there I saw it; my mother's eyes.

Eyes that I was terrified of. Ever since I scar myself, I wear contact lenses to avoid looking at her eyes. I avoided her, looking at her crying is too much. Too much.
.
.
.
I woke up the next day still in the bathroom, my eyes were red, my body was sore. And I still remember that day as clear as day. I picked up my phone and called my dad "Dad, I'm going to be a police officer."
.
.
.
5 days later a package came. A handgun. There was initials written; 'H.W.' Harold Wiltroops.

I stared at it and smiled
"This is a dream long gone, thanks mom".
[ASH's BACKSTORY ENDS] a/n: his brother moved to Japan not long after

caption.text:
#ep_recruit1entry #ep_recruit1cv FINALLY DONE. But... I'm not satisfied with this one. I honestly think I could've done better for the background. BUT ANYWAY

Name: Lashkay "Ash" Wiltroops
Gender: Female
Age: 22
Nationality: Sweden
Personality: Quiet, sarcastic. Her sarcasms are always so under-the-radar people wouldn't notice
Weapons: Handgun (from her dad), knife (she put them in a pocket that circles her thigh), smoke bombs (her belt is custom made and she kept them there)

Ash is an analyst, she wished all her life to be so. Her dad was a policeman and he taught her shooting since age 5. Her mom already died when she was only 6 months old, car crash. She has an older brother who lived out of town and sometimes do visit her.

Ash is now live alone in her apartment. Her dad is out there somewhere working in US, chief of the drug department.

Ash suffers from Alexandria's Genesis, a "disease" that makes her eyes purple-colored. (FYI look it up! It's a real disease, a cool one). For now, that's her background story.

Mom: wake up, it's morning, you got extra lessons today right?

*Silence*
Mom: *tickling me again* just how handsome will your husband be, huh? Hahaha *Still tickling*
Me: *roll to her* foreigner.
Mom: *laughs and tells me to wake up*

So, yeah it's true. I was kinda half-asleep but I know what I was saying tho.
